description: Describes available Amazon Web Services services in a prefix list format, which includes the prefix list name and prefix list ID of the service and the IP address range for the service. We recommend that you use  DescribeManagedPrefixLists instead.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: One or more filters. prefix-list-id: The ID of a prefix list. prefix-list-name: The name of a prefix list. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. If you specify multiple filters, the filters are joined with an AND, and the request returns only results that match all of the specified filters. For more information, see List and filter using the CLI and API in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. Name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. Values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. If you specify multiple values for a filter, the values are joined with an OR, and the request returns all results that match any of the specified values. (string) ---

parameters.name: PrefixListIds
parameters.description: One or more prefix list IDs. (string) ---

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to use to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.

nested_items.name: Cidrs
nested_items.description: The IP address range of the Amazon Web Services service.
